			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Uptime IT Systems is a growing and entrepreneurial organization dedicated to providing the best possible customer service experience. We strive to hire team members who enjoy solving problems, interacting with people, and who are committed to continual professional development.</p>
<p>
	Uptime is currently seeking its next Help Desk Engineer. The Help Desk Engineer is responsible for resolving customer service support requests relating to desktops, laptops, servers, and networking hardware and software as well as assisting field engineers with project implementation.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Deliver outstanding remote/phone support, with a focus on being empathetic to customer concerns/frustrations, setting appropriate expectations, and backing up promises with action</li>
	<li>
		Assist less experienced support engineers with an emphasis on enhancing their ability to solve problems before escalation</li>
	<li>
		Create clear and concise documentation for solutions to problems and common system administration procedures for use by the entire support team</li>
	<li>
		Maintain accurate time entries, ticket notes, and other documentation in Uptime&#39;s internal systems</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Eager learner who picks up new technologies easily and can become proficient in a short time</li>
	<li>
		Excellent troubleshooting capability</li>
	<li>
		Strong verbal/written communications skills</li>
	<li>
		Understanding of technology common in a small business environment, most importantly Microsoft software products</li>
	<li>
		Bachelors Degree in related field or equivalent experience</li>
	<li>
		Ability to work flexible 8-hour shift&nbsp;(beginning as early as <span data-scayt_word="7am" data-scaytid="1">7am</span>, ending as late as <span data-scayt_word="7pm" data-scaytid="2">7pm</span>) as may be assigned</li>
	<li>
		Available for occasional after hours or weekend project work</li>
	<li>
		Ability to achieve relevant vendor certifications</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Experience in LAN/network/systems administration or help desk role</li>
	<li>
		Experience with professional services automation system (<span data-scayt_word="Connectwise" data-scaytid="3">Connectwise</span>) and&nbsp;remote management and monitoring platform (<span data-scayt_word="Kaseya" data-scaytid="4">Kaseya</span>)</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
